Subject: Use CompatibleSingleApp instead of SingleApplication
Upstream: No (custom patch for Wolfi/Debian packaging)
Origin: https://salsa.debian.org/mendezr/stremio
Author: Juan Manuel MÃ©ndez Rey <vejeta@gmail.com>

This patch replaces the upstream SingleApplication dependency with
CompatibleSingleApp, a custom Qt single-instance implementation that
provides similar functionality without requiring external dependencies.

CompatibleSingleApp uses Qt's built-in QLocalServer/QLocalSocket to
ensure only one instance of Stremio runs at a time, communicating
between instances when needed.

---
--- a/mainapplication.h
+++ b/mainapplication.h
@@ -1,6 +1,6 @@
 #include <QEvent>
 #include <QFileOpenEvent>
-#include "singleapplication.h"
+#include "compatible_singleapp.h"
 #include "autoupdater.h"

 #ifdef Q_OS_MACOS
@@ -8,7 +8,7 @@
 #define APP_TYPE QApplication
 #else
-#define APP_TYPE SingleApplication
+#define APP_TYPE CompatibleSingleApp
 #endif
